1
00:00:00,559 --> 00:00:05,890
Does it feel time and time again like you
are being watched and your stops are being

2
00:00:05,890 --> 00:00:06,890
hunted?

3
00:00:06,890 --> 00:00:08,050
Then you are not alone.

4
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:11,360
This is a common complaint of many retail
traders.

5
00:00:11,360 --> 00:00:16,139
The problem is that you probably are entering
at the wrong times in the market.

6
00:00:16,139 --> 00:00:22,310
Today we’ll fix this and I’ll share a
very simple scalping and day trading strategy,

7
00:00:22,310 --> 00:00:24,349
to trade any market.

8
00:00:24,349 --> 00:00:30,239
The concept of the strategy is derived from
the 2 major phases of price movement: expansion

9
00:00:30,239 --> 00:00:31,669
and contraction.

10
00:00:31,669 --> 00:00:41,080
So, like, subscribe, and stick around for
the full video.

11
00:00:41,080 --> 00:00:45,980
Contraction/expansion
Markets go through periods of contraction

12
00:00:45,980 --> 00:00:51,340
when prices move in narrow range while traders’
interest comes down.

13
00:00:51,340 --> 00:00:55,030
These periods of narrow range are called contraction.

14
00:00:55,030 --> 00:01:00,210
When markets are doing nothing, they are giving
a message: we have a balance between bulls

15
00:01:00,210 --> 00:01:01,470
and bears.

16
00:01:01,470 --> 00:01:05,159
Neither is strong enough to take the market
in their direction.

17
00:01:05,159 --> 00:01:10,609
Soon enough, one of these forces – either
the bulls or the bears will emerge as the

18
00:01:10,609 --> 00:01:12,509
stronger force.

19
00:01:12,509 --> 00:01:17,069
Then comes a period of expansion, when the
winning force will take the market sharply

20
00:01:17,069 --> 00:01:20,729
in its favor, trapping the losing force.

21
00:01:20,729 --> 00:01:27,479
This is the period when markets will move
outside the previous ranges, in one direction.

22
00:01:27,479 --> 00:01:33,380
Inside bar contraction

23
00:01:33,380 --> 00:01:38,789
Identifying the waves of contraction and expansion
is a powerful skill to have and one of the

24
00:01:38,789 --> 00:01:44,040
simplest way to find these periods is by analyzing
inside bars.

25
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:49,179
Inside bars on a candlestick chart represent
the consolidation of price action where the

26
00:01:49,179 --> 00:01:54,799
bulls and bears are both struggling to move
the price higher or lower from its current

27
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:56,039
position.

28
00:01:56,039 --> 00:02:02,049
You can easily spot an inside bar when a given
bar’s high and low are fully contained by

29
00:02:02,049 --> 00:02:05,280
the bar directly preceding it.

30
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:11,009
This signals a narrowing of price action,
a contraction that can be used to anticipate

31
00:02:11,009 --> 00:02:14,819
upcoming movements outside of this range.

32
00:02:14,819 --> 00:02:19,560
Basically, when there is contraction, pressure
is building.

33
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:28,879
Double inside bar trick
On their own, inside bars can be quite tricky,

34
00:02:28,879 --> 00:02:31,319
especially if you are unexperienced.

35
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:37,280
You can find hundreds of inside bars during
a trading day, if you trade lower time frames.

36
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:43,110
A double inside bar setup will solve this
problem and will highlight the period of contraction

37
00:02:43,110 --> 00:02:44,640
even better.

38
00:02:44,640 --> 00:02:50,329
A double inside bar is when there are two
consecutive ‘inside bars’ which have failed

39
00:02:50,329 --> 00:02:54,120
to breach the high and low of the previous
bar.

40
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:57,799
It reflects contraction and indecision.

41
00:02:57,799 --> 00:03:03,720
This price action set-up, although rare, is
more significant than just an inside bar.

42
00:03:03,720 --> 00:03:09,860
The colors of the bars are irrelevant – the
fact that we have two consecutive bars inside

43
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:15,140
the previous bars range is the main aspect
here.

44
00:03:15,140 --> 00:03:18,510
Double inside bars are a rare contraction
signal.

45
00:03:18,510 --> 00:03:22,270
So rare, it would be a shame to miss the opportunity!

46
00:03:22,270 --> 00:03:27,510
You can trade both trend continuations and
key reversals.

47
00:03:27,510 --> 00:03:33,590
If this setup is present at a key technical
level, maybe a key support, at a round number

48
00:03:33,590 --> 00:03:40,230
or a FIB level, or at a pivot level, or near
a moving average, it can often reflect a change

49
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:41,519
in sentiment.

50
00:03:41,519 --> 00:03:44,470
And a great opportunity for you to take advantage
of.

51
00:03:44,470 --> 00:03:48,000
We’ll cover many scenarios later in the
video.

52
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:53,019
If there is no technical level in the way,
then the safest way is to trade the setup

53
00:03:53,019 --> 00:03:57,439
as a continuation one, with the prevailing
trend.

54
00:03:57,439 --> 00:04:05,890
Inside bar indicator
Let’s simplify the process of searching

55
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:11,620
and analyzing candlesticks, and let’s use
an indicator which displays inside bars.

56
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,370
I use this one.

57
00:04:13,370 --> 00:04:18,280
It finds and reveals all inside bars on the
chart.

58
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:24,630
Your job is to simply find the double inside
bar setup, when you see two consecutive arrows.

59
00:04:24,630 --> 00:04:29,930
Here’s the trading plan:
• In a trending market, you will trade only

60
00:04:29,930 --> 00:04:34,650
with the trend, by trading continuation breakouts.

61
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:41,380
• In a range bound market, you will sell
the top of the range and buy the bottom

62
00:04:41,380 --> 00:04:47,060
In both cases, the location of the double
inside bar is very important.

63
00:04:47,060 --> 00:04:49,930
My preferred locations to trade are near:
1.

64
00:04:49,930 --> 00:04:51,930
Levels of support and resistance
2.

65
00:04:51,930 --> 00:04:52,970
Trend lines
3.

66
00:04:52,970 --> 00:04:54,280
Moving averages
4.

67
00:04:54,280 --> 00:04:55,800
Fibonacci levels
5.

68
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:57,759
Daily Pivots
6.

69
00:04:57,759 --> 00:05:00,259
Round numbers

70
00:05:00,259 --> 00:05:05,870
We trade Bitcoin, on the 5 minutes time frame.

71
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:13,509
We see a clear downtrend, with price making
lower lows and lower highs.

72
00:05:13,509 --> 00:05:16,740
And now we are in a range.

73
00:05:16,740 --> 00:05:23,300
In this case I would prefer short trades,
in the direction of the dominant trend.

74
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:28,340
Here’s our double inside bar setup.

75
00:05:28,340 --> 00:05:33,780
As we are near the resistance level of the
range, the plan is to short a breakout to

76
00:05:33,780 --> 00:05:37,000
the downside.

77
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:41,020
Price broke the upper level of the channel,
but we ignore the signal.

78
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:45,940
Remember, you don’t want to fight the existing
trend.

79
00:05:45,940 --> 00:05:51,389
Next candle brought a downside breakout, so
we entered short.

80
00:05:51,389 --> 00:05:57,370
Stop loss goes on the other side of the channel,
or above the previous swing high.

81
00:05:57,370 --> 00:06:01,970
It all depends on the size of the channel
and recent price action.

82
00:06:01,970 --> 00:06:07,830
As for take profits, as I’m trading the
5 minutes charts and I’m scalping, I target

83
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:11,639
the next swing in the price structure, at
least.

84
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:17,389
In this case this swing.

85
00:06:17,389 --> 00:06:22,900
Then you can use a trailing stop, a breakeven
stop, or whatever money management technique

86
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,750
you prefer.

87
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:30,600
But your trade should offer a positive risk
to reward ratio.

88
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:35,449
Now we see another double inside bar below
the first signal.

89
00:06:35,449 --> 00:06:43,400
As we are already in a trade, we ignore this
one.

90
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:50,729
Let’s find another trade.

91
00:06:50,729 --> 00:06:54,949
Price again seemed to form another range,
again, in a downtrend.

92
00:06:54,949 --> 00:06:58,919
So, we’ll keep looking to sell the market.

93
00:06:58,919 --> 00:07:07,430
Here’s our signal, 2 consecutive inside
bars.

94
00:07:07,430 --> 00:07:13,780
If we zoom out, we see that the signal appeared
below this breakout.

95
00:07:13,780 --> 00:07:19,771
This seems like a break and retest situation,
and the location of the double inside bar

96
00:07:19,771 --> 00:07:23,190
setup favors a short trade.

97
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:29,009
Here’s our breakout.

98
00:07:29,009 --> 00:07:36,240
Stop loss on the other side of the channel,
or above this swing high.

99
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:42,580
As we are already very near the previous swing
low, we expect price to break it and to continue

100
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:43,800
the downtrend.

101
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:56,650
Let’s try a risk to reward ratio of 3, but
we’ll keep an eye on price action.

102
00:07:56,650 --> 00:08:00,700
Another good trade and we even left some profits
on the table.

103
00:08:00,700 --> 00:08:08,259
Again, you can play with the take profit,
and try different techniques.

104
00:08:08,259 --> 00:08:15,120
Let’s continue.

105
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:25,419
Here’s our signal.

106
00:08:25,419 --> 00:08:30,190
We have a double bottom here and a small break
of structure.

107
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:37,050
But at the same time, the setup appear at
this swing high, in a downtrend.

108
00:08:37,050 --> 00:08:40,279
So, this situation isn’t so clear.

109
00:08:40,279 --> 00:08:45,630
I still favor the short trade, but if the
breakout occurs to the upside, I’ll still

110
00:08:45,630 --> 00:08:47,560
risk a long trade.

111
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:55,410
Okey, we have a downward breakout, so a short
trade it is.

112
00:08:55,410 --> 00:09:00,980
Stop loss above this swing high, above the
channel.

113
00:09:00,980 --> 00:09:12,550
Take profit at this swing low, a few points
above it.

114
00:09:12,550 --> 00:09:30,980
Let’s change the market, let’s trade GBP/USD,
and let’s add a moving average.

115
00:09:30,980 --> 00:09:37,570
If price is above the 200 EMA, you’ll trade
only long breakouts above the double inside

116
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:45,010
bar setup
If price is below the 200 EMA, you’ll trade

117
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:48,940
only short breakouts below the double inside
bar pattern

118
00:09:48,940 --> 00:10:03,720
In this example, price is below the 200 EMA,
so in this case we’ll target short positions.

119
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:08,420
Here’s the signal.

120
00:10:08,420 --> 00:10:14,130
We have consecutive inside bars around this
resistance area.

121
00:10:14,130 --> 00:10:22,250
We have a triple rejection in a small amount
of time.

122
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:30,220
As price broke the channel to the downside,
we entered short with a stop above the channel

123
00:10:30,220 --> 00:10:33,010
and a take profit around this swing low.

124
00:10:33,010 --> 00:10:44,450
That’s a risk to reward ratio of 2.

125
00:10:44,450 --> 00:10:46,970
We move on.

126
00:10:46,970 --> 00:10:58,579
Price broke above the 200 EMA, so now we are
looking to buy the market.

127
00:10:58,579 --> 00:11:01,990
And here’s the signal to enter.

128
00:11:01,990 --> 00:11:10,540
Consecutive inside bars, right at the 200
EMA.

129
00:11:10,540 --> 00:11:14,350
You buy here, at the breakout of the channel.

130
00:11:14,350 --> 00:11:18,860
Stop loss below the channel and below the
200 EMA.

131
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:21,310
Take profit at the next swing high.

132
00:11:21,310 --> 00:11:30,170
That’s a risk to reward ratio of 4.

133
00:11:30,170 --> 00:11:36,350
We lost the trade, despite the fact it was
actually a pretty good signal.

134
00:11:36,350 --> 00:11:44,430
Let’s once again change the market and trade
Tesla.

135
00:11:44,430 --> 00:11:52,170
I see a downtrend, lower lows, lower highs.

136
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:55,620
And here’s the double inside bar pattern.

137
00:11:55,620 --> 00:12:05,019
I favor short trades, but if price breaks
to the upside, I’ll still take a long trade.

138
00:12:05,019 --> 00:12:10,850
The pressure remained to the downside, so
we had a downward breakout, in line with the

139
00:12:10,850 --> 00:12:14,820
previous trend.

140
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:21,399
Stop goes above this swing high and we target
the previous swing low.

141
00:12:21,399 --> 00:12:34,980
This offers a risk to reward ratio of 2.3.

142
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:40,709
Another signal, after we closed the previous
trade with a profit.

143
00:12:40,709 --> 00:12:49,680
The location of the pattern, below the previous
swing low, favors another short trade.

144
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:57,550
Which indeed happened, as price broke once
again the previous low.

145
00:12:57,550 --> 00:13:01,000
Stop loss above the channel.

146
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:06,160
As we don’t have an immediate swing low
to target, we set a risk to reward ratio of

147
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:11,230
2.

148
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:22,450
The beauty of double inside bars is that they
can be traded as both continuations and key

149
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:23,450
reversals.

150
00:13:23,450 --> 00:13:26,089
And it’s all price action based.

151
00:13:26,089 --> 00:13:31,649
By scanning the market for trends that are
in place, you can start to identify periods

152
00:13:31,649 --> 00:13:38,500
of price contraction where a trend has stopped
making higher highs and higher lows in a bullish

153
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:44,380
trend, and lower lows and lower highs in a
bearish trend.

154
00:13:44,380 --> 00:13:50,630
When price breaks from these contracted areas,
it reveals that either the buyers or sellers

155
00:13:50,630 --> 00:14:18,149
have regained control of the trend and can
help you time your entry and ride 

156
00:14:18,149 --> 00:15:09,009
the momentum.

157
00:15:09,009 --> 00:15:15,269
This is not a perfect strategy, you will encounter
losing trades and for this reason you could

158
00:15:15,269 --> 00:15:21,829
put your own spin on it, additional confirmations
or other types of analysis.

159
00:15:21,829 --> 00:15:27,829
If you can back up consecutive inside bars
with other technical tools, it might be worth

160
00:15:27,829 --> 00:15:30,660
opening a position.

161
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:36,220
Just make sure you don’t overcomplicate
it and stick to the main concepts of this

162
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:44,480
strategy: finding periods of contraction and
ride the momentum move after the breakout.

163
00:15:44,480 --> 00:15:50,510
As always, if you learned something new and
found value, leave us a like to show your

164
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:51,529
support.

165
00:15:51,529 --> 00:15:57,649
And check out our academy program, if you
want to further level up your trading.

166
00:15:57,649 --> 00:15:58,370
Until next time.

